Data Preprocessing-Before Building Machine learning model¶

Steps of preprocessing of data¶

step:1]-Import necessary library step:2]-Read Dataset step:3]-sanity check of data step:4]-Exploratory Data Analysis(EDA) step:5]-Missing Value treatments step:6]-Outliers treatments step:7]-duplicates & garbage value treatments step:8]-Normalization step:9]-Encoding of data

Step.6]-Outliers treatments¶

In [ ]:
#decide whether to do outliers treatment or not ,if do how?
In [138]:
def wisker(col):
    q1,q3=np.percentile(col,[25,75])
    iqr=q3-q1
    lw=q1-1.5*iqr
    uw=q3+1.5*iqr
    return lw,uw
In [140]:
wisker(df['GDP'])
Out[140]:
(-9773.52021495771, 17837.165679596183)
In [156]:
for i in ['GDP','Total expenditure','thinness 5-9 years','thinness  1-19 years']:
    lw,uw=wisker(df[i])
    df[i]=np.where(df[i]<lw,lw,df[i])
    df[i]=np.where(df[i]>uw,uw,df[i])
